   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1866_02_16_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_W_Brummer_Amsterdam_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>W. Brummer<lb/>AMSTERDAM-ROTTERDAM.</p>
         <p>per Messag. Imperiales<lb/>Messrs.<lb/>L. Kniffler +Co, Yokohama<lb/>Amsterdam 16th
                Feb. 1866<lb/>Since my respectful letter from 9th of this month I have had the
                <lb/>pleasure of receiving your esteemed letter from 16th Dec., the content <lb/>of
                which I have taken note of._<lb/>The main reason for today’s letter is to send in to
                you at the request[?]<lb/>of your Mr. Louis Kniffler the enclosed documents about
                the inspection<lb/>of the 1,950[?] cocoons._ I am further enclosing a copy of the
                letter by<lb/>Messrs. Geb Mayer + Co as a guideline if you please.__ Your Mr.<lb/>L.
                K. has had the same documents; he answered, via myself, the <lb/>letter by Messrs.
                Meyer and will likely report more details to you <lb/>soon. __<lb/>Upon looking up
                the letter I noticed a mistake in the sums<lb/>in your sales invoice from 17th March
                1865 for W.B.<lb/>1[?]/28, 28 boxes of shirtings from the “Cymbeline” at #21 to my
                <lb/>detriment, for which I debited you per the Guilder account with f. 287½<lb/>
         </p>
         <table rend="rules">
            <row>
               <cell rend="left">
                  <p rend="Table text (9)" style="text-align:left;">⟨ft!⟩</p>
               </cell>
               <cell rend="left">f. 61.90. (At #21 are added 2½% bill of exchange
                        charges)</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
               <cell rend="left"/>
               <cell rend="left">＂ 1.87. Interest at 5[?]% from 28 Mai/31. Dec</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
               <cell rend="left"/>
               <cell rend="left">f<hi rend="underline">63.77. per January 1866.-</hi>
               </cell>
            </row>
         </table>
         <p>However, I credited you with your half of the insurance moneys received <lb/>for 7
                bundles of canvas by means of the “Libea”</p>
         <table rend="rules">
            <row>
               <cell rend="left">tra 1%[?]<lb/>⟨Mem fol 105⟩</cell>
               <cell rend="left">f. 489.09</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
               <cell rend="left"/>
               <cell rend="left">＂ 4.91</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
               <cell rend="left"/>
               <cell rend="left">f493.11 per 10th February</cell>
            </row>
         </table>
         <p>The Orleans[?] sales at #10 are again leaving quite a big loss. <lb/>Given the
                shortage of taffachelas I hope that you are going to put<lb/>those that you still
                have to the most profitable use,</p>
         <pb facs="1866_02_16_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_W_Brummer_Amsterdam_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <p>similarly the shirtings of silk, which will surely have<lb/>arrived and been sold
                with a nice profit by now. <lb/>I have great hopes for this and it is indeed about
                time <lb/>or at least there is a need that our friend van Oam<lb/>gets a calculation
                for once in which a profit has been made, <lb/>which has not happened so
                far.-<lb/>As a consequence of the favourable reports about taffachelas<lb/>shirtings
                I am now hoping for new shipments although<lb/>my friends are wretchedly
                disheartened. -<lb/>Cotton Midl Upland 19d 8¼ Mergreg[?]<lb/>Skirtings 17/6 to
                17/.-<lb/>Money remains terribly expensive and the market tends<lb/>more towards an
                increase of the discount than towards a<lb/>reduction.- London 8%, Amsterdam 7 to
                7½%.__<lb/> All agents of the houses there have new designs[?]-<lb/>for taffachelas-
                with wide stripes; I have not received <lb/>any from you forever and a day, which
                means that my <lb/>Rott[erdam] house missed out on an offer of 2,500 pcs. by E. S.
                Zuck,<lb/>which are now going to another house!<lb/>In fact one can see new things
                here almost every day, <lb/>sent here from Japan!__<lb/>Your friend<lb/>
            <hi rend="underline">W. Brummer</hi>
         </p>
         <pb facs="1866_02_16_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_W_Brummer_Amsterdam_3.tif" n="3"/>
